<P>THE GLEANER.</P>
<P>A MISCELLANEOUS PRODUCTION. IN THREE VOLUMES.</P>
<P>BY CONSTANTIA.</P>
<Q><L>Slow to <HI>condemn&punc;</HI> and <HI>&s;eeking to commend,</HI></L>
<L><HI>Good &s;en&s;e</HI> will with deliberation &s;can;</L>
<L>To <HI>trivial</HI> faults unwilling to de&s;cend,</L>
<L>If <HI>Virtue</HI> gave, and form'd the general plan.</L></Q>
<P>VOL. I.</P>
<P>Publi&s;hed according to Act of Congre&s;s.</P>
<P>PRINTED AT <HI>BOSTON,</HI> BY I. THOMAS AND E. T. ANDREWS, FAUST's STATUE, No. 45, Newbury-Street.</P>
